dme.forecastiolib

Class FIODataPoint

  • java.lang.Object
    • dme.forecastiolib.FIODataPoint

  • public class FIODataPoint
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a Forecast.io Data Point.
    It contains all the available fields in a forecast.
    Author:
    David Ervideira, Theo FIDRY

      • getMoonPhase

        public final long getMoonPhase()
                        throws JSONSlotNotFoundException
        Get a number representing the fractional part of the lunation number of the given day. This can be thought of as the “percentage complete” of the current lunar month: a value of 0 represents a new moon, a value of 0.25 represents a first quarter moon, a value of 0.5 represents a full moon, and a value of 0.75 represents a last quarter moon
        Returns:
        Throws:
        JSONSlotNotFoundException

      • getNearestStormDistance

        public final long getNearestStormDistance()
                                   throws JSONSlotNotFoundException
        Get numerical value representing the distance to the nearest storm in miles. (This value is very approximate and should not be used in scenarios requiring accurate results. In particular, a storm distance of zero doesn’t necessarily refer to a storm at the requested location, but rather a storm in the vicinity of that location.)
        Returns:
        Throws:
        JSONSlotNotFoundException

      • getNearestStormBearing

        public final long getNearestStormBearing()
                                  throws JSONSlotNotFoundException
        Get a numerical value representing the direction of the nearest storm in degrees, with true north at 0° and progressing clockwise. (If nearestStormDistance is zero, then this value will not be defined. The caveats that apply to nearestStormDistance also apply to this value.)
        Returns:
        Throws:
        JSONSlotNotFoundException

      • getPrecipitationIntensity

        public final long getPrecipitationIntensity()
                                     throws JSONSlotNotFoundException
        Get a numerical value representing the average expected intensity (in inches of liquid water per hour) of precipitation occurring at the given time conditional on probability (that is, assuming any precipitation occurs at all). A very rough guide is that a value of 0 in./hr. corresponds to no precipitation, 0.002 in./hr. corresponds to very light precipitation, 0.017 in./hr. corresponds to light precipitation, 0.1 in./hr. corresponds to moderate precipitation, and 0.4 in./hr. corresponds to heavy precipitation.
        Returns:
        Throws:
        JSONSlotNotFoundException

      • getCloudCover

        public final long getCloudCover()
                         throws JSONSlotNotFoundException
        Get a numerical value between 0 and 1 (inclusive) representing the percentage of sky occluded by clouds. A value of 0 corresponds to clear sky, 0.4 to scattered clouds, 0.75 to broken cloud cover, and 1 to completely overcast skies.
